import requests

url = "https://us-south.ml.cloud.ibm.com/ml/v1/text/generation?version=2023-05-29"

body = {
	"input": """I request to know  the meaning of deep learning from a surgeon  point of view.


Deep learning is a subset of machine learning, which is essentially a neural network with three or more layers. These neural networks attempt to simulate the behavior of the human brain—albeit far from matching its complexity—in order to \"learn\" from large amounts of data. While a neural network with a single layer can still make approximate predictions, additional hidden layers can help optimize the accuracy.

Deep learning models are built with a large number of layers, allowing the system to learn and make decisions based on increasingly complex patterns in the data. This hierarchical structure enables deep learning models to uncover intricate relationships within data and make accurate predictions even with large datasets.

Deep learning algorithms are trained using a process called backpropagation, which involves computing the gradient of the error function with respect to the weights and biases of the model. By iteratively adjusting these parameters, the model minimizes the error and improves its predictive capabilities.

Deep learning has been successful in various domains, including computer vision, natural""",
	"parameters": {
		"decoding_method": "greedy",
		"max_new_tokens": 200,
		"repetition_penalty": 1
	},
	"model_id": "ibm/granite-13b-chat-v2",
	"project_id": "3fd3bbd0-6d18-4d81-b7ce-ff5b0f2a6c78",
	"moderations": {
		"hap": {
			"input": {
				"enabled": True,
				"threshold": 0.5,
				"mask": {
					"remove_entity_value": True
				}
			},
			"output": {
				"enabled": True,
				"threshold": 0.5,
				"mask": {
					"remove_entity_value": True
				}
			}
		}
	}
}

headers = {
	"Accept": "application/json",
	"Content-Type": "application/json",
	"Authorization": "Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN"
}

response = requests.post(
	url,
	headers=headers,
	json=body
)

if response.status_code != 200:
	raise Exception("Non-200 response: " + str(response.text))

data = response.json()

# End of code

